---
import Body from "@components/Body.astro";
import Footer from "@components/Footer.astro";
import BaseHead from "@components/head/BaseHead.astro";
import ImportHead from "@components/head/ImportHead.astro";
import MainHead from "@components/head/MainHead.astro";
import PreloadHead from "@components/head/PreloadHead.astro";
import Layout from "@layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <head>
    <BaseHead />
    <PreloadHead />
    <ImportHead>
      <style>
        section {
          padding-top: 0.7rem;
          padding-bottom: 0.7rem;
        }
      </style>
      <script>
        import { Collapse } from "bootstrap";
      </script>
    </ImportHead>
    <MainHead
      title="Support Me"
      description="Help me work on and improve mastercomfig!"
    />
  </head>
  <Body>
    <div class="container">
      <section>
        <a href="/">
          <small
            ><span class="fas fa-arrow-left fa-fw"></span> Back to home</small
          >
        </a>
        <br />
        <div class="py-2">
          <img
            style="height:32px;width:32x;vertical-align:bottom"
            src="/img/mastercomfig_logo_transparent_i.svg"
            alt="logo"
          />
          <span style="font-size: 1.5rem" class="text-secondary"
            >mastercomfig</span
          >
        </div>
        <h1 class="display-4">Support Me</h1>
        <hr />
        <p class="lead">
          Running mastercomfig takes a lot of time, effort and money. If you
          appreciate any of my work, please consider supporting me!
        </p>
        <div class="progress">
          <div
            class="progress-bar progress-bar-animated"
            role="progressbar"
            style="width: 8%"
            aria-valuenow="8"
            aria-valuemin="0"
            aria-valuemax="100"
          >
          </div>
          <div
            class="progress-bar progress-bar-animated"
            role="progressbar"
            style="width: 37%;background-color: rgb(156, 39, 176, 0.3)"
            aria-valuenow="37"
            aria-valuemin="0"
            aria-valuemax="100"
          >
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center">
          <span class="text-muted">$0</span>
          <span class="text-muted">$1,459.20</span>
        </div>
        <br />
        <p>
          mastercomfig has <span class="text-primary">received</span>
          <strong>8% ($127.22)</strong> of its funding needs for <strong
            >2026</strong
          >. We are <span class="text-info">projected</span> to reach <strong
            >37% ($544.64)</strong
          > by the end of the year if current funding levels continue.
        </p>
        <h3>Monthly Costs</h3>
        <p>
          I have provided the following information for full transparency of the
          monthly costs of running mastercomfig. I rely on support from the
          community to be able to afford to keep the website and services
          online.
        </p>
        <p>
          Total cost per month: <strong>$121.60</strong>. This amounts to <strong
            >$1,459.20 per year</strong
          >.
        </p>
        <p>
          <a
            id="collapseCostButton"
            class="collapse-button"
            data-bs-toggle="collapse"
            href="#collapseCost"
            role="button"
            aria-expanded="false"
            aria-controls="collapseCost"
          >
            <span class="fas fa-chevron-down fa-fw"></span> View cost breakdown
          </a>
        </p>
        <div class="collapse" id="collapseCost">
          <div class="collapse-wrapper">
            <ul>
              <li>
                <strong>CloudFlare: $25/month</strong> - Provides hosting for web
                services, security and DDoS protection
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Google Cloud Storage: $1/month</strong> - Provides cloud
                storage for web assets, like hitsounds
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Sentry: $41/month</strong> - Provides error tracking, crash
                reporting, performance monitoring, and other logs to help us improve
                the web services and Team Comtress 2
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Dedicated servers: $38.40/month</strong> - Provides hosting
                for Team Comtress 2 game servers
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>VPS: $14.20/month</strong> - Provides hosting for mastercomfig
                web services like quickplay and Discord bots used for community features
                and service notifications / syncing
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Domain: $6/month</strong> - Provides domain names (comfig.app,
                mastercomfig.com, teamcomtress.com, quickplay.tf) for comfig app
                and other sites
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Ko-Fi Gold: $6/month</strong> - Used to accept payments from
                the community
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p>
          We also have some other costs which are considered optional. If there
          is not enough support to keep the project funds healthy, we cancel
          these services to stabilize costs. These optional costs total <strong
            >$75.50 per month</strong
          >, or <strong>$906 per year</strong>.
        </p>
        <p>
          <a
            id="collapseCostOptionalButton"
            class="collapse-button"
            data-bs-toggle="collapse"
            href="#collapseCostOptional"
            role="button"
            aria-expanded="false"
            aria-controls="collapseCostOptional"
          >
            <span class="fas fa-chevron-down fa-fw"></span> View optional costs
          </a>
        </p>
        <div class="collapse" id="collapseCostOptional">
          <div class="collapse-wrapper">
            <ul>
              <li>
                <strong>Discord Server Boosts: $31/month</strong> - Used for the
                comfig Discord server, to provide users with a higher upload limit
                for sharing during help requests, and for the Discord vanity link
                to help with discoverability
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Double Counter Pro: $8.50/month</strong> - Used to enhance
                security against bots and scams for the comfig Discord server
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Dyno Premium: $6/month</strong> - Used for moderation features
                in the comfig Discord server, and help with tech support
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Google Cloud Compute: $30/month</strong> - Used to host 100
                player and other TF2 server events for the community and for testing
                new performance features. Previously, these experiments led to the
                development of features to help power all 100 player servers, including
                shounic's trenches, enabling servers to provide a much better gameplay
                experience.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <small
          >Note: These costs have been averaged to represent monthly costs, some
          of which are paid at different intervals.</small
        >
        <br />
        <br />
        <p>
          And of course, this says nothing of the time I spend on all the
          projects and maintaining them, but I love what I do and I am very
          grateful when I can even break even on this.
        </p>
      </section>
      <section>
        <h3>Monetary Support</h3>
        <p>
          You can support me with direct financial contributions through the
          following services:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="https://ko-fi.com/mastercoms">Ko-fi</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://www.patreon.com/mastercoms">Patreon</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://liberapay.com/mastercoms">Liberapay</a></li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://github.com/sponsors/mastercoms">GitHub Sponsors</a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a
              href="https://discord.com/servers/mastercomfig-389089828249010188"
              >Discord Supporter</a
            >
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>
      <section>
        <h3>Gifts</h3>
        <p>
          You can gift me things through Steam!<p>
            <ul>
              <li>
                Gift me items through <a
                  href="https://steamcommunity.com/tradeoffer/new/?partner=85845165&token=M9cQHh8N"
                  >trade offers</a
                >
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              Or, you can gift me Steam games or Wallet funds. Just first add me
              as a friend on <a href="https://steamcommunity.com/id/mastercoms/"
                >Steam</a
              > (leave a comment about gifting!), then:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>
                Gift me a <a
                  href="https://store.steampowered.com/digitalgiftcards/selectgiftcard"
                  >Steam Digital Card</a
                >
              </li>
              <li>
                Gift me a game from my <a
                  href="https://store.steampowered.com/wishlist/profiles/76561198046110893/#sort=price"
                  >wishlist</a
                >
              </li>
            </ul>

            <p>
              Or, if you want to give me something more physical, you can gift
              me Amazon items through
              <a href="https://throne.com/mastercoms">Throne</a>.
            </p>
          </p>
        </p>
      </section>
      <section>
        <h3>tradeit.gg</h3>
        <p>
          Thanks to tradeit.gg's generosity and interest in the Team Fortress 2
          community, they have sponsored me with an affiliate link. If you
          purchase items through this link, you will get a $5 topup bonus for
          any trades/purchases you make, and I receive 1% of the value of your
          purchase as a commission.
        </p>
        <p>
          To me, I definitely think we need more variety and competition in the
          TF2 trading/market space. While there seems to be a premium on some
          items available on tradeit.gg, I can only imagine as more users join,
          the supply will increase and prices will be more competitive. And, I
          think their more sustainable and fair business model is worth
          supporting, vs. other sites that are known to be shady or prey on
          unsuspecting users.
        </p>
        <p>
          <a href="https://tradeit.gg/?ref=comfig"
            >Get started on tradeit.gg today and receive your $5 credit.</a
          >
        </p>
      </section>
      <section>
        <h3>Epic Games Creator</h3>
        <p>
          If you cannot directly support me, I have a
          <a
            href="https://www.epicgames.com/fortnite/en-US/news/support-a-creator-faq"
            >Support-A-Creator</a
          > code: <code>mastercoms</code>, which you can set in
          <a
            href="https://www.epicgames.com/fortnite/en-US/news/support-a-creator-faq"
            >Fortnite</a
          >, <a href="https://www.rocketleague.com/support-a-creator/"
            >Rocket League</a
          >, and other games on the
          <a href="https://store.epicgames.com/">Epic Games Store</a>, as well
          as purchasing games and DLC on the store itself. In connection with
          Epic Gamesâ€™ Support-A-Creator Program, I receive a commission from
          these purchases.
        </p>
      </section>
      <section>
        <h3>Fortnite Maps</h3>
        <p>
          You can also play on my Fortnite maps, which give me money based on
          engagement:
        </p>
        <p>
          <a href="https://www.fortnite.com/@mastercoms/7761-6157-7902"
            ><img
              class="img-fluid"
              style="max-width: 500px"
              src="https://docs.comfig.app/dev/assets/images/staredown.webp"
              alt="staredown preview"
            /></a
          >
          <br />
          <strong>
            <a href="https://www.fortnite.com/@mastercoms/7761-6157-7902"
              >Staredown - 8v8 TDM</a
            ></strong
          > Island code: <code>7761-6157-7902</code>
          <br /><br />
          <a href="https://www.fortnite.com/@mastercoms/4173-4839-7557"
            ><img
              class="img-fluid"
              style="max-width: 500px"
              src="/img/support_me/combatlab.webp"
              alt="orange combat sandbox preview"
            /></a
          >
          <br />
          <strong>
            <a href="https://www.fortnite.com/@mastercoms/4173-4839-7557"
              >Orange Combat Sandbox - 16v16 arena</a
            ></strong
          > Island code: <code>4173-4839-7557</code>
          <br /><br />
          <a href="https://www.fortnite.com/@mastercoms/4173-4839-7557"
            ><img
              class="img-fluid"
              style="max-width: 500px"
              src="/img/support_me/dpsmode.webp"
              alt="1v1 Tracking Aim Trainer preview"
            /></a
          >
          <br />
          <strong>
            <a href="https://www.fortnite.com/@mastercoms/4173-4839-7557"
              >1v1 Tracking Aim Trainer</a
            ></strong
          > Island code: <code>4173-4839-7557</code>
        </p>
      </section>
      <section>
        <h3>Thank You!</h3>
        <p>
          You have my endless gratitude if you support me with money or gift
          items, and this support encourages me so much!
        </p>
        <p>
          If you cannot support me through the above methods, that's fine too!
          Your thank yous are always cherished and mean so much to me!
        </p>
      </section>
      <hr />
      <Footer />
    </div>
  </Body></Layout
>
